<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head lang="en">
	    <meta charset="UTF-8">
	    <title>BossyUI Styles</title>
	    <link href="dist/css/bossy.css" rel="stylesheet">
	    {LRScript|s}
	    <style>
				.container {
					margin-left: auto;
					margin-right: auto;
					max-width: 1024px;
				}
	    </style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<header>
			<div class="container">
				<h1>Bossy UI Styles</h1>
			</div>
		</header>

		<div class="container">
			<div class="grid">
				<div class="col-1-4">
					<nav>
						<ul class="unstyle">
							<li><a href="#tiles">Tiles</a></li>
							<li><a href="#bars">Bars</a></li>
							<li><a href="#buttons">Buttons</a></li>
						</ul>
					</nav>
				</div>
				<div class="col-3-4">
					<section id="tiles" class="tile">
						<header class="bar">
							<h2>Tiles</h2>
						</header>

						<div class="grid">
					    <div class="col-1-3">
					      <section class="tile" style="height: 100px;">
					      </section>
					    </div>
					    <div class="col-2-3">
					      <h3 id="tiles">Tiles</h3>
					      <p>
					        Tiles are structural elements, visual building blocks for contained elements on the page. Tiles should be used when a piece of information needs to visually separate from others around it.
					      </p>
					    </div>
					  </div>
					  <div class="grid">
					    <div class="col-1-3">
					      <section class="tile--stacked" style="height: 100px;">
					      </section>
					      <section class="tile--stacked" style="height: 100px;">
					      </section>
					    </div>
					    <div class="col-2-3">
					      <h3>Stacked Tiles</h3>
					      <p>
					        Tiles can also be stacked together. Instead of <code>.tile</code> use <code>.tiles--stacked</code> and the negative space between the tile elements will collapse.
					      </p>
					    </div>
					  </div>
					</section>

					<section id="bars" class="tile">
						<header class="bar">
							<h2>Bars</h2>
						</header>
					  <div class="grid">
					    <div class="col-1-3">
					      <div class="bar">
					        <span>Bar Default</span>
					        <button class="bar-button">&#10005</button>
					      </div>

					      <div class="bar--primary">
					        <span>Bar Primary</span>
					        <button class="bar-button">&#10005</button>
					      </div>

					      <div class="bar--secondary">
					        <span>Bar Secondary</span>
					        <button class="bar-button">&#10005</button>
					      </div>
					    </div>
					    <div class="col-2-3">
					      <p>Bars are a visual container for specific content. They can be used as headers, footers or interactive elements. Their primary purpose is to provide a visual labeling mechanism and a single interactive button.</p>
					    </div>
					  </div>
					</section>

					<section id="buttons" class="tile">
						<header class="bar"><h2>Buttons</h2></header>
					  <div class="grid">
					  	<div class="col-1-3">
					  		<button>Single Button</button>
					  		<div class="group">
					  			<button>Group</button>
					  			<button>Group</button>
					  			<button>Group</button>
					  		</div>
					  	</div>
					  	<div class="col-2-3">

					  	</div>
					  </div>
					</section>

				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>